4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Tallapoosa County; to authorize the
10 collection and expenditure of a fee for remote access of
11 records; and to ratify and confirm prior collection and
12 expenditure of fees.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. This act shall only apply in Tallapoosa
15 County.
16 Section 2. (a) The Tallapoosa County Judge of Probate
17 may charge and collect an additional fee for the remote access
18 of records in the office of the judge of probate by computer
19 or other electronic or digital system.
20 (b) Fees collected pursuant to subsection (a) shall be
21 deposited into the special indexing fund of the Tallapoosa
22 County Judge of Probate or any successor special fund under
23 the control of the judge of probate. The funds shall be used
24 for the maintenance, operation, and improvement of the office,
25 including, but not limited to, the recording system and
26 remote-access services.
27 (c) The judge of probate shall have discretion to
28 determine the appropriate use of these funds for the general
Page 1

